cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a method for density map estimation, localization, and tracking in dense crowds of video clips captured by drones. The method uses a multi-scale attention network and is trained in an end-to-end manner with a multi-task loss. The paper falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with video analysis and object tracking. It also falls under robotics (cs.RO) as it deals with drone-based data collection and tracking. The use of attention networks and multi-task learning suggests that it may also fall under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the use of video clips and trajectory generation suggests that it may also fall under multimedia (cs.MM).
